verbose_text: Patients were grouped on the basis of upper and lower levels of Ca, 25OHD and iPTH for assessing parathyroid dysfunction into primary hypoparathyroidism [low calcium (Ca) & intact parathyroid hormone (iPTH)], sub-clinical hypoparathyroidism [low iPTH and 25 hydroxy vitamin D (25OHD), low / normal Ca], normal functioning parathyroid gland [Normal Ca, iPTH and 25OHD] and secondary hyperparathyroidism [high iPTH, low / normal Ca and/or 25OHD].
